com.wizarpos.devices
Interface OperationResult

All Known Subinterfaces:
ContactlessCardOperationResult, IDCardOperationResult, MSROperationResult, PINPadOperationResult, SCSOperationResult, SerialOperationResult
public interface OperationResult

Operation results are generated by a device implementation to notify the application of the completion of a requested operation.

OperationResult serves as a pattern for all Operation Events. For each specific service package, an interface must be derived from OperationResult which adds methods allowing the application to access data appropriate for that device and result.

The getStatus method is used by the application to retrieve the success of the operation. The following values are defined in OperationResult for this purpose:

ST_NONE No operation is pending. This is a placeholder initialization value for pre-created events.
ST_SUCCESS The operation was completed successfully.
ST_ERROR An error occurred during operation processing; the operation was not completed.
ST_CANCEL The operation was externally cancelled; the operation was not completed.

When an operation result is received and its status is ST_ERROR, the getInfo method may be used to retrieve the specific type or cause of the error. Constants are defined in OperationResult for some of these errors. Constants for device-specific information are defined in the operation result interface in the control package defined for each service control.

Note that the error information constants in OperationResult are assigned negative values. Those defined in individual device control packages may then assume any positive value without fear of conflict.

The following error information constants are defined in OperationResult:

ERR_GENERAL_ERROR A catastrophic error has occurred during an asynchronous operation, preventing even the security rights from being tested. This is the highest-priority error designation.
ERR_NO_PERMISSION The requested operation is not available. This could be because the application has no permission of this operation.
ERR_NO_INFO This code is used with an error event when no further information is available. This information code must be set by a service implementation if the cause of the error does not fit an error description in the service documentation.
ERR_TIMEOUT The error resulted from the expiration of a timeout.
